## SDK v3 OFFICIAL RULES (source: apps-sdk-v3.developer.homey.app)

### Manager Access Pattern (MANDATORY)
```javascript
// SDK v3: Access managers through this.homey.<managerId>
this.homey.drivers.getDriver('my-driver');  // ManagerDrivers
this.homey.flow.getDeviceTriggerCard('id'); // ManagerFlow
this.homey.settings.get('key');             // ManagerSettings

// WRONG (SDK v2 global Managers — will crash):
// Homey.ManagerDrivers, ManagerSettings, etc.
```

### Async Requirements (MANDATORY)
- `async onNodeInit()` — Zigbee device initialization (NOT onInit)
- `await this.setCapabilityValue()` — MUST be awaited
- `async onPair()`, `async onDiscovery()` — all pairing methods async
- NO `.then()` callbacks for SDK v3 methods — use async/await

### Memory Management (Homey Pro 2023 critical)
- Every `registerCapabilityListener` must be idempotent on restart
- Avoid listener duplication when device reconnects/restarts
- Clear timeouts in `onDeleted()` or `onUninit()`
- Max ~8 listeners per device before memory review needed

### CI Semantic Linter Safety
- NEVER auto-modify driver files in CI — report-only mode
- Don't blindly pipe AI output into source files
- SDK v3 linter checks: async init, Manager globals, v2 API, await setCapability, listener leaks, settings keys, titleFormatted

